## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of recent data and the inherent complexity of economic systems, which can make it challenging to isolate the effects of minimum wage changes from other economic variables. Additionally, the impact of minimum wage adjustments can vary significantly across different regions and industries, making generalizations difficult. Further research with updated data and more localized studies would provide a clearer picture of the minimum wage's economic impact.